    "preparations_description": "The main herbal preparations of Borinda strigosa are derived from its leaves and twigs, which contain flavonoids and phenolic acids. Tea is prepared by steeping the leaves in hot water, while infusion involves steeping the leaves in cold water, both used to treat fever and gastrointestinal issues. Decoction is made by boiling the twigs in water to treat respiratory problems and sore throats. Tincture is prepared by soaking the leaves in ethanol to treat digestive issues, and salve is made by mixing the leaves with a carrier oil to treat wounds and skin conditions. These preparations are chosen for their anti-inflammatory, antimicrobial, and antioxidant properties found in Borinda strigosa.",
